@node Main "Arrowz - Documentation"

                              'Arrowz' 1.1

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Arrowz' is a Workbench @{" game " link play} where your goal is to rotate arrows
between a 'pressed down' space and a coloured tile like the one shown
on the uppermost position in the column displayed at the right of the
game board. When the arrows form a way to the required tile, a path is
then formed (all the arrows used to make that path are pressed down)
to that tile. That tile then becomes the next starting space.

  The more arrows that are used to make a path between the two tiles,
the more points you will make, but beware! There are 'holes' that must
be avoided, and if the arrows are positioned in such a way that they
lead to a hole, the game is over.

  Continue to get to the other coloured tiles until you finish each
game board.

  Have fun!

