@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Arrowz" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play it's very simple, click on any arrow, this will make it turn
clockwise by 90 degrees. Turn the arrows until they make a path to a tile
that has the same pattern as the one shown on the uppermost position in
the column to the right of the game board.

  When a path has been completed, all the arrows used to reach the
coloured tile will be 'pressed down' and that tile will become the next
'starting' tile. Then, the next coloured tile will become the tile to
reach for.

  Continue the game until there are no more tiles to reach for, and the
game will display a new game board.

  As you use arrows to make a path between the starting tile and the
'wanted' tile, the more arrows you use to complete that path, the more
points you get. The scoring goes like this:

  1 arrow  = 1 point
  2 arrows = 3 points
  3 arrows = 6 points
  4 arrows = 10 points
  etc.

  Beware of the holes (the octagonal shapes) that are located on the
board, because if the arrows point to a hole, the game is over.

  Have fun!

